{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":721,"text":"Of the five senses, vision is the one\nthat I appreciate the most,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and it's the one that I can\nleast take for granted."},{"time":7650,"text":"I think this is partially due\nto my father, who was blind."},{"time":10575,"text":"It was a fact that he didn't make\nmuch of a fuss about, usually."},{"time":13702,"text":"One time in Nova Scotia, when we went\nto see a total eclipse of the sun --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":17360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":18402,"text":"Yeah, same one as in the Carly Simon song,"},{"time":20515,"text":"which may or may not refer\nto James Taylor, Warren Beatty"},{"time":23363,"text":"or Mick Jagger; we're not really sure."},{"time":25219,"text":"They handed out these dark plastic viewers"},{"time":27779,"text":"that allowed us to look\ndirectly at the sun"},{"time":29852,"text":"without damaging our eyes."},{"time":31143,"text":"But Dad got really scared;\nhe didn't want us doing that."},{"time":33903,"text":"He wanted us instead to use\nthese cheap cardboard viewers,"},{"time":36785,"text":"so that there was no chance at all\nthat our eyes would be damaged."},{"time":40469,"text":"I thought this was\na little strange at the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42763,"text":"What I didn't know at the time"},{"time":44255,"text":"was that my father had actually\nbeen born with perfect eyesight."},{"time":47337,"text":"When he and his sister Martha\nwere just very little,"},{"time":50020,"text":"their mom took them out\nto see a total eclipse --"},{"time":52522,"text":"or actually, a solar eclipse --"},{"time":54077,"text":"and not long after that, both of them\nstarted losing their eyesight."},{"time":58382,"text":"Decades later, it turned out\nthat the source of their blindness"},{"time":61868,"text":"was most likely some sort\nof bacterial infection."},{"time":64700,"text":"As near as we can tell,\nit had nothing whatsoever to do"},{"time":67355,"text":"with that solar eclipse,"},{"time":69302,"text":"but by then my grandmother\nhad already gone to her grave"},{"time":71994,"text":"thinking it was her fault."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74517,"text":"So, Dad graduated Harvard in 1946,"},{"time":77518,"text":"married my mom,"},{"time":78700,"text":"and bought a house\nin Lexington, Massachusetts,"},{"time":80955,"text":"where the first shots were fired\nagainst the British in 1775,"},{"time":84569,"text":"although we didn't actually hit\nany of them until Concord."},{"time":87668,"text":"He got a job working for Raytheon\ndesigning guidance systems,"},{"time":91266,"text":"which was part of the Route 128\nhigh-tech axis in those days --"},{"time":94342,"text":"so, the equivalent\nof Silicon Valley in the '70s."},{"time":97583,"text":"Dad wasn't a real\nmilitaristic kind of guy;"},{"time":99966,"text":"he just felt bad that he wasn't able\nto fight in World War II"},{"time":103135,"text":"on account of his handicap,"},{"time":104809,"text":"although they did let him get through"},{"time":106615,"text":"the several-hour-long army physical exam"},{"time":110376,"text":"before they got to the very last test,\nwhich was for vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113422,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116088,"text":"So Dad started racking\nup all of these patents"},{"time":119263,"text":"and gaining a reputation as a blind\ngenius, rocket scientist, inventor."},{"time":122756,"text":"But to us he was just Dad,\nand our home life was pretty normal."},{"time":127343,"text":"As a kid, I watched a lot of television"},{"time":129262,"text":"and had lots of nerdy hobbies\nlike mineralogy and microbiology"},{"time":132924,"text":"and the space program\nand a little bit of politics."},{"time":135468,"text":"I played a lot of chess."},{"time":136712,"text":"But at the age of 14, a friend\ngot me interested in comic books,"},{"time":139879,"text":"and I decided that was\nwhat I wanted to do for a living."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143146,"text":"So, here's my dad:"},{"time":144954,"text":"he's a scientist, he's an engineer\nand he's a military contractor."},{"time":150855,"text":"So, he has four kids, right?"},{"time":152678,"text":"One grows up to become\na computer scientist,"},{"time":154806,"text":"one grows up to join the Navy,"},{"time":156758,"text":"one grows up to become an engineer ..."},{"time":159024,"text":"And then there's me:\nthe comic book artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162008,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165762,"text":"Which, incidentally, makes me\nthe opposite of Dean Kamen,"},{"time":168474,"text":"because I'm a comic book artist,\nson of an inventor,"},{"time":170960,"text":"and he's an inventor,\nson of a comic book artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173319,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":174572,"text":"Right? It's true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175759,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178437,"text":"The funny thing is,\nDad had a lot of faith in me."},{"time":180796,"text":"He had faith in my abilities\nas a cartoonist,"},{"time":182972,"text":"even though he had no direct evidence\nthat I was any good whatsoever;"},{"time":186283,"text":"everything he saw was just a blur."},{"time":187974,"text":"Now, this gives a real meaning\nto the term \"blind faith,\""},{"time":190710,"text":"which doesn't have the same\nnegative connotation for me"},{"time":193326,"text":"that it does for other people."},{"time":194823,"text":"Now, faith in things which cannot\nbe seen, which cannot be proved,"},{"time":197991,"text":"is not the sort of faith that I've ever\nreally related to all that much."},{"time":201740,"text":"I tend to like science,"},{"time":203191,"text":"where what we see and can ascertain\nare the foundation of what we know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208651,"text":"But there's a middle ground, too --"},{"time":210803,"text":"a middle ground tread by people\nlike poor old Charles Babbage"},{"time":214382,"text":"and his steam-driven computers\nthat were never built."},{"time":217834,"text":"Nobody really understood\nwhat it was that he had in mind"},{"time":220907,"text":"except for Ada Lovelace,"},{"time":223160,"text":"and he went to his grave\ntrying to pursue that dream."},{"time":226978,"text":"Vannevar Bush with his memex --"},{"time":229398,"text":"this idea of all of human\nknowledge at your fingertips --"},{"time":232399,"text":"he had this vision."},{"time":233951,"text":"And I think a lot of people in his day"},{"time":235817,"text":"probably thought he was a bit of a kook."},{"time":237780,"text":"And, yeah, we can look back\nin retrospect and say,"},{"time":240219,"text":"\"Yeah, ha-ha, it's all microfilm --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":242464,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":243511,"text":"But that's not the point;\nhe understood the shape of the future."},{"time":246621,"text":"So did J.C.R. Licklider and his notions\nfor computer-human interaction."},{"time":251235,"text":"Same thing: he understood\nthe shape of the future,"},{"time":254128,"text":"even though it was something\nthat would only be implemented"},{"time":257754,"text":"by people much later."},{"time":259169,"text":"Or Paul Baran, and his vision\nfor packet switching."},{"time":261912,"text":"Hardly anybody listened to him in his day."},{"time":264771,"text":"Or even the people\nwho actually pulled it off,"},{"time":266987,"text":"the people at Bolt, Beranek\nand Newman in Boston,"},{"time":269621,"text":"who just would sketch out these structures"},{"time":272557,"text":"of what would eventually\nbecome a worldwide network,"},{"time":275117,"text":"and sketching things on the back\nof napkins and on note papers"},{"time":278759,"text":"and arguing over dinner\nat Howard Johnson's --"},{"time":281081,"text":"on Route 128 in Lexington, Massachusetts,"},{"time":283495,"text":"just two miles from where I was studying\nthe Queen's Gambit Deferred"},{"time":286752,"text":"and listening to Gladys Knight &amp; The Pips"},{"time":288876,"text":"singing \"Midnight Train to Georgia\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291068,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292095,"text":"in my dad's big easy chair, you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293961,"text":"So, three types of vision, right?"},{"time":295922,"text":"Vision based on what one cannot see,"},{"time":298923,"text":"the vision of that unseen and unknowable."},{"time":301716,"text":"The vision of that which has already\nbeen proven or can be ascertained."},{"time":305200,"text":"And this third kind, a vision of something\nwhich can be, which may be,"},{"time":311749,"text":"based on knowledge\nbut is, as yet, unproven."},{"time":315477,"text":"Now, we've seen a lot\nof examples of people"},{"time":317555,"text":"who are pursuing\nthat sort of vision in science,"},{"time":319897,"text":"but I think it's also true\nin the arts, it's true in politics,"},{"time":322875,"text":"it's even true in personal endeavors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325087,"text":"What it comes down to, really,\nis four basic principles:"},{"time":327760,"text":"learn from everyone;"},{"time":328983,"text":"follow no one;"},{"time":330811,"text":"watch for patterns;"},{"time":332659,"text":"and work like hell."},{"time":333862,"text":"I think these are the four principles\nthat go into this."},{"time":336906,"text":"And it's that third one, especially,"},{"time":338761,"text":"where visions of the future\nbegin to manifest themselves."},{"time":342429,"text":"What's interesting is that this particular\nway of looking at the world,"},{"time":345828,"text":"is, I think, only one\nof four different ways"},{"time":347984,"text":"that manifest themselves\nin different fields of endeavor."},{"time":350724,"text":"In comics, I know that it results\nin sort of a formalist attitude"},{"time":355231,"text":"towards trying to understand how it works."},{"time":357314,"text":"Then there's another,\nmore classical attitude"},{"time":359569,"text":"which embraces beauty and craft;"},{"time":362176,"text":"another one which believes\nin the pure transparency of content;"},{"time":366232,"text":"and then another, which emphasizes\nthe authenticity of human experience"},{"time":370203,"text":"and honesty and rawness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371645,"text":"These are four very different ways\nof looking at the world."},{"time":374473,"text":"I even gave them names:"},{"time":375649,"text":"the classicist, the animist,\nthe formalist and iconoclast."},{"time":378420,"text":"Interestingly, they seem\nto correspond more or less"},{"time":380984,"text":"to Jung's four subdivisions\nof human thought."},{"time":383579,"text":"And they reflect a dichotomy\nof art and delight"},{"time":386391,"text":"on left and the right;"},{"time":387630,"text":"tradition and revolution\non the top and the bottom."},{"time":390154,"text":"And if you go on the diagonal,\nyou get content and form,"},{"time":392821,"text":"and then beauty and truth."},{"time":394086,"text":"And it probably applies just as much\nto music and movies and fine art,"},{"time":398196,"text":"which has nothing whatsoever\nto do with vision at all,"},{"time":401197,"text":"or, for that matter, nothing to do\nwith our conference theme"},{"time":404102,"text":"of \"Inspired by Nature,\""},{"time":405458,"text":"except to the extent\nof the fable of the frog"},{"time":408162,"text":"who gives a ride to the scorpion\non his back to get across the river"},{"time":411454,"text":"because the scorpion\npromises not to sting him,"},{"time":413688,"text":"but the scorpion stings him anyway\nand they both die,"},{"time":416246,"text":"but not before the frog asks\nhim why, and the scorpion says,"},{"time":419159,"text":"\"Because it's my nature.\""},{"time":420382,"text":"In that sense, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421561,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424930,"text":"So this was my nature."},{"time":426184,"text":"The thing was, I saw that the route I took"},{"time":429322,"text":"to discovering this focus in my work"},{"time":433191,"text":"and who I was --"},{"time":435059,"text":"I saw it as just this road to discovery."},{"time":437310,"text":"Actually, it was just me\nembracing my nature,"},{"time":439557,"text":"which means that I didn't actually fall\nthat far from the tree, after all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445540,"text":"So what does a \"scientific mind\"\ndo in the arts?"},{"time":450540,"text":"I started making comics, but I also\nstarted trying to understand them,"},{"time":453955,"text":"almost immediately."},{"time":455130,"text":"One of the most important things\nabout comics that I discovered"},{"time":458236,"text":"was that comics are a visual medium,"},{"time":460107,"text":"but they try to embrace\nall of the senses within it."},{"time":463073,"text":"So, the different elements\nof comics, like pictures and words,"},{"time":467164,"text":"and the different symbols\nand everything in between"},{"time":469706,"text":"that comics presents,"},{"time":470917,"text":"are all funneled through\nthe single conduit, a vision."},{"time":473509,"text":"So we have things like resemblance,"},{"time":475510,"text":"where something which resembles\nthe physical world can be abstracted"},{"time":478774,"text":"in a couple of different directions:"},{"time":480560,"text":"abstracted from resemblance,\nbut still retaining the complete meaning,"},{"time":484184,"text":"or abstracted away\nfrom both resemblance and meaning"},{"time":486925,"text":"towards the picture plane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488205,"text":"Put all these three together,\nand you have a nice little map"},{"time":491063,"text":"of the entire boundary\nof visual iconography,"},{"time":493202,"text":"which comics can embrace."},{"time":495011,"text":"And if you move to the right\nyou also get language,"},{"time":497873,"text":"because that's abstracting\neven further from resemblance,"},{"time":500874,"text":"but still maintaining meaning."},{"time":503477,"text":"Vision is called upon to represent sound"},{"time":506251,"text":"and to understand\nthe common properties of those two"},{"time":509846,"text":"and their common heritage as well;"},{"time":512010,"text":"also, to try to represent\nthe texture of sound"},{"time":514419,"text":"to capture its essential\ncharacter through visuals."},{"time":519136,"text":"There's also a balance between the visible\nand the invisible in comics."},{"time":524159,"text":"Comics is a kind of call and response,"},{"time":526080,"text":"in which the artist gives you something\nto see within the panels,"},{"time":529246,"text":"and then gives you something\nto imagine between the panels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533025,"text":"Also, another sense\nwhich comics' vision represents,"},{"time":537314,"text":"and that's time."},{"time":538984,"text":"Sequence is a very important\naspect of comics."},{"time":542652,"text":"Comics presents a kind of temporal map."},{"time":545946,"text":"And this temporal map was something\nthat energizes modern comics,"},{"time":549606,"text":"but I was wondering\nif perhaps it also energizes"},{"time":552551,"text":"other sorts of forms,"},{"time":554093,"text":"and I found some in history."},{"time":556606,"text":"You can see this same principle operating"},{"time":559314,"text":"in these ancient versions\nof the same idea."},{"time":562322,"text":"What's happening is,"},{"time":563499,"text":"an art form is colliding\nwith a given technology,"},{"time":565865,"text":"whether it's paint on stone,"},{"time":567230,"text":"like the Tomb of Menna the Scribe\nin ancient Egypt,"},{"time":569651,"text":"or a bas-relief sculpture\nrising up a stone column,"},{"time":572279,"text":"or a 200-foot-long embroidery,"},{"time":574331,"text":"or painted deerskin and tree bark"},{"time":576332,"text":"running across 88 accordion-folded pages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578794,"text":"What's interesting is,\nonce you hit \"print\" --"},{"time":580983,"text":"and this is from 1450, by the way --"},{"time":582864,"text":"all of the artifacts of modern comics\nstart to present themselves:"},{"time":586021,"text":"rectilinear panel arrangements,"},{"time":587561,"text":"simple line drawings without tone,"},{"time":589353,"text":"and a left-to-right reading sequence."},{"time":592763,"text":"And within 100 years, you already start\nto see word balloons and captions,"},{"time":597795,"text":"and it's really just a hop, skip\nand a jump from here to here."},{"time":601509,"text":"So I wrote a book about this in '93,\nbut as I was finishing the book,"},{"time":604968,"text":"I had to do a little bit of typesetting,"},{"time":606908,"text":"and I was tired of going\nto my local copy shop to do it,"},{"time":609600,"text":"so I bought a computer."},{"time":610869,"text":"And it was just a little thing --"},{"time":612567,"text":"it wasn't good for much\nexcept text entry --"},{"time":614757,"text":"but my father had told me\nabout Moore's law back in the '70s,"},{"time":618621,"text":"and I knew what was coming."},{"time":620549,"text":"And so, I kept my eyes peeled"},{"time":623271,"text":"to see if the sort\nof changes that happened"},{"time":625336,"text":"when we went from pre-print\ncomics to print comics"},{"time":627970,"text":"would happen when we went beyond,\nto post-print comics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631335,"text":"So, one of the first things proposed"},{"time":633107,"text":"was that we could mix\nthe visuals of comics"},{"time":635485,"text":"with the sound, motion\nand interactivity of the CD-ROMs"},{"time":638320,"text":"being made in those days."},{"time":639550,"text":"This was even before the Web."},{"time":641153,"text":"And one of the first things they did was,"},{"time":643138,"text":"they tried to take the comics page as is"},{"time":645073,"text":"and transplant it to monitors,"},{"time":646557,"text":"which was a classic McLuhanesque mistake"},{"time":648582,"text":"of appropriating the shape\nof the previous technology"},{"time":651105,"text":"as the content of the new technology."},{"time":653190,"text":"And so, what they would do\nis have these comic pages"},{"time":655694,"text":"that resemble print comics pages,"},{"time":657353,"text":"and they would introduce\nall this sound and motion."},{"time":659793,"text":"The problem was that if you go\nwith this basic idea"},{"time":663058,"text":"that space equals time in comics,"},{"time":665430,"text":"what happens is that\nwhen you introduce sound and motion,"},{"time":668169,"text":"which are temporal phenomena\nthat can only be represented through time,"},{"time":671592,"text":"they break with that continuity\nof presentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676820,"text":"Interactivity was another thing."},{"time":678386,"text":"There were hypertext comics,\nbut the thing about hypertext"},{"time":681177,"text":"is that everything in hypertext\nis either here, not here,"},{"time":683910,"text":"or connected to here;"},{"time":685092,"text":"it's profoundly nonspatial."},{"time":686466,"text":"The distance from Abraham Lincoln\nto a Lincoln penny"},{"time":688943,"text":"to Penny Marshall to the Marshall Plan\nto \"Plan 9\" to nine lives:"},{"time":692052,"text":"it's all the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693227,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694444,"text":"But in comics,"},{"time":697320,"text":"every aspect of the work,\nevery element of the work,"},{"time":700214,"text":"has a spatial relationship\nto every other element at all times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703373,"text":"So the question was:"},{"time":704565,"text":"Was there any way to preserve\nthat spatial relationship"},{"time":707566,"text":"while still taking advantage\nof all of the things"},{"time":709938,"text":"that digital had to offer us?"},{"time":711605,"text":"And I found my personal answer for this"},{"time":713660,"text":"in those ancient comics\nthat I was showing you."},{"time":715994,"text":"Each of them has a single\nunbroken reading line,"},{"time":719358,"text":"whether it's going zigzag across the walls\nor spiraling up a column"},{"time":723075,"text":"or just straight left to right,"},{"time":724627,"text":"or even going in a backwards zigzag\nacross those 88 accordion-folded pages,"},{"time":728700,"text":"the same thing is happening;"},{"time":730118,"text":"that is, that the basic idea\nthat as you move through space"},{"time":732928,"text":"you move through time,"},{"time":734107,"text":"is being carried out\nwithout any compromise,"},{"time":736215,"text":"but there were compromises when print hit."},{"time":738270,"text":"Adjacent spaces were no longer\nadjacent moments,"},{"time":741210,"text":"so the basic idea of comics\nwas being broken again and again"},{"time":744453,"text":"and again and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745633,"text":"And I thought, OK, well, if that's true,"},{"time":747983,"text":"is there any way,\nwhen we go beyond today's print,"},{"time":750914,"text":"to somehow bring that back?"},{"time":754065,"text":"Now, the monitor is just as limited\nas the page, technically, right?"},{"time":759326,"text":"It's a different shape,\nbut other than that,"},{"time":761477,"text":"it's the same basic limitation."},{"time":763406,"text":"But that's only if you look\nat the monitor as a page,"},{"time":766969,"text":"but not if you look\nat the monitor as a window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769691,"text":"And that's what I propose,"},{"time":770962,"text":"that perhaps we could create\nthese comics on an infinite canvas,"},{"time":774103,"text":"along the X axis and the Y axis"},{"time":777037,"text":"and staircases."},{"time":778834,"text":"We could do circular narratives\nthat were literally circular."},{"time":781764,"text":"We could do a turn in a story\nthat was literally a turn."},{"time":785206,"text":"Parallel narratives\ncould be literally parallel."},{"time":788977,"text":"X, Y and also Z."},{"time":792239,"text":"So I had all these notions."},{"time":793585,"text":"This was back in the late '90s,"},{"time":795117,"text":"and other people in my business\nthought I was pretty crazy,"},{"time":797972,"text":"but a lot of people then went on\nand actually did it."},{"time":800521,"text":"I'm going to show you a couple now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802763,"text":"This was an early collage comic\nby a fellow named Jasen Lex."},{"time":809636,"text":"And notice what's going on here."},{"time":811435,"text":"What I'm searching for\nis a durable mutation --"},{"time":813979,"text":"that's what all of us are searching for."},{"time":815980,"text":"As media head into this new era,"},{"time":819184,"text":"we are looking for mutations\nthat are durable,"},{"time":821700,"text":"that have some sort of staying power."},{"time":825237,"text":"Now, we're taking this basic idea\nof presenting comics in a visual medium,"},{"time":829365,"text":"and we're carrying it through all the way\nfrom beginning to end."},{"time":832700,"text":"That's that entire comic you just saw,\nup on the screen right now."},{"time":835895,"text":"But even though we're only experiencing it\none piece at a time,"},{"time":838978,"text":"that's just where\nthe technology is right now."},{"time":841584,"text":"As the technology evolves,"},{"time":843346,"text":"as you get full immersive\ndisplays and whatnot,"},{"time":846354,"text":"this sort of thing\nwill only grow; it will adapt."},{"time":849148,"text":"It will adapt to its environment;\nit's a durable mutation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854725,"text":"Here's another one."},{"time":855914,"text":"This is by Drew Weing; this is called"},{"time":858235,"text":"\"'Pup' Ponders the Heat Death\nof the Universe.\""},{"time":886062,"text":"See what's going on here"},{"time":888579,"text":"as we draw these stories\non an infinite canvas"},{"time":893835,"text":"is you're creating a more pure expression\nof what this medium is all about."},{"time":903660,"text":"We'll go by this a little quickly.\nYou get the idea."},{"time":906257,"text":"I just want to get to the last panel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914045,"text":"[Cat 1: Pup! Earth to Pup!\nCat 2: Come play baseball with us!]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":917165,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":918252,"text":"[Pup: Did either of you realize"},{"time":919876,"text":"that eventually the universe\nwill be nothing but a thin, cold gas"},{"time":923195,"text":"spread across infinite, lonely space?]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":925179,"text":"[Cat 1: Oh ...\nCat 2: We'd better hurry, then!]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":927825,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931517,"text":"Just one more."},{"time":935144,"text":"Talk about your infinite canvas."},{"time":937113,"text":"It's by a guy named\nDaniel Merlin Goodbrey, in Britain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940263,"text":"Why is this important?"},{"time":942898,"text":"I think this is important because media --"},{"time":946397,"text":"all media --"},{"time":947763,"text":"provide us a window back into our world."},{"time":950568,"text":"Now, it could be that motion pictures\nand eventually, virtual reality,"},{"time":954914,"text":"or something equivalent to it,\nsome sort of immersive display,"},{"time":958117,"text":"is going to provide us\nwith our most efficient escape"},{"time":962258,"text":"from the world that we're in."},{"time":963700,"text":"That's why most people turn\nto storytelling, to escape."},{"time":966504,"text":"But media provides us with a window\nback into the world we live in."},{"time":973255,"text":"And when media evolve"},{"time":976422,"text":"so that the identity of the media\nbecomes increasingly unique --"},{"time":981423,"text":"because what you're looking at\nis comics cubed,"},{"time":984647,"text":"you're looking at comics\nthat are more comics-like"},{"time":987046,"text":"than they've ever been before --"},{"time":988665,"text":"when that happens, you provide\npeople with multiple ways"},{"time":991341,"text":"of reentering the world\nthrough different windows."},{"time":995343,"text":"And when you do that, it allows them\nto triangulate the world they live in"},{"time":999134,"text":"and see its shape."},{"time":1000533,"text":"That's why I think this is important."},{"time":1002334,"text":"One of many reasons,\nbut I've got to go now."},{"time":1004413,"text":"Thank you for having me."}]}]}